                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>London</placeName>
                                        <date>10th <add>?</add> 5611</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>14 March 1851</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">It was with no little anxiety that I daily<lb/>
                                        looked for the arrival of our good friend <persName>Revd. Mr
                                                  Isaacs</persName> (which took place this<lb/> day
                                        a fortnight) both for himself as well as to obtain precise
                                        news from you<lb/> it was shortly after on the Evening I had
                                        an interview with him—he dined with me<lb/> on the
                                                  <date>Tuesday</date>, and you may easily suppose
                                        that the chief topic on both meetings<lb/> which truly
                                        interested me was your affair. He delivered me your letter.
                                        I am<lb/> truly mortified at your present state and
                                        situation! <add>אחי אחי</add> my dear brother<lb/> I will
                                        exclaim, is this the reward after 20 years labour?
                                                  <add>בעבודת הקדש זו תורה וזו שכרה</add><lb/> I am
                                        further wounded to find the result <del>such</del> of my
                                        letters such, so important, strongly<lb/> argued, and indeed
                                        such feeling ones which I addressed <persName>Mr. A.
                                                  Hart</persName> on your<lb/> behalf <add>אמרתי
                                                  לריק יגעתי</add>, my first one to him was with all
                                        the <hi rend="underline">dignities</hi> &amp; <hi
                                                  rend="underline">honors</hi> of <hi
                                                  rend="underline">Parnas</hi>,<lb/> and indeed he
                                        must have communicated it to his colleagues &amp; friends
                                        for on<lb/> some of my observations he says this. "Neither
                                        contention or schism exist or is<lb/> likely to exist in our
                                        midst and your letter is the first intimation to myself<lb/>
                                        and the board of managers of such an event." Any passage in
                                        any part of<lb/> my correspondence you are at full liberty
                                        to show only <hi rend="underline">such passages</hi>
                                        which<lb/> might be of advantage to you, but I solemnly
                                        protest that in <hi rend="underline">no way
                                        whatever</hi><lb/> touching any individual such as
                                                  <persName>Mr Morais</persName> &amp;c (as he is a
                                        friend) and any <sic>triffling</sic><lb/> information must
                                        be kept sacred and in no way my name mingled; trusting<lb/>
                                        to your honor and <hi rend="underline">integrity</hi> that
                                        such passages at all times will be kept<lb/> confidentially;
                                                  <add>סוד ה' ליראיו</add> Our friend
                                                  <persName>Isaacs</persName> he is a truly good
                                        &amp; honest man<lb/> I have known something of him before
                                        his departure for <placeName>America</placeName>, but
                                        my<lb/> intimacy was then with his brother
                                                  <persName>David</persName>, their father was a
                                        worthy person <add>תם וישר וירא אלקים/הולך יושר</add><lb/>
                                        <add>ודי למבין</add>. <persName>Revd S</persName> I see is
                                        this day absent, gone to <placeName>Holland</placeName> to
                                        the same relative<lb/> on his return to
                                                  <placeName>America</placeName> he will give you a
                                        correct and precise account of our English<lb/> Jews, that
                                        which I have <hi rend="underline">pointed</hi> out to him,
                                        and he himself has witnessed<lb/> the state of affairs; <hi
                                                  rend="underline">flattery</hi>, <hi
                                                  rend="underline">emptiness</hi> and similar
                                                  <sic>saleable</sic> articles only;</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p><hi rend="underline">no man</hi> in this world would I be so happy
                                        as to embrace and make my<lb/> friend and companion like
                                        yourself—we have not your equal here who can<lb/> work for
                                        the Jew cause as yourself, your learning, your information;
                                        but it is<lb/> not a market for <hi rend="underline">genuine
                                                  Gold</hi>. They <sic>dont</sic> want it, anything
                                                  <hi rend="underline">brass</hi>, <hi
                                                  rend="underline">copper</hi> &amp;c<lb/> so that
                                        it has a gloss <add>דרך אמונה</add> as for literature
                                                  <sic>dont</sic> talk of it. I know what my<lb/>
                                        old friend the great <persName>Solomon Bennett</persName>
                                        suffered who had <hi rend="underline">sterling</hi> works,
                                        was it not for<lb/> the Christian friends would his work on
                                        the Temple &amp; Engraving be out—or his<lb/> judge by my
                                                  <hi rend="underline">small</hi> &amp;
                                                  <sic>triffling</sic> portion of the <add>נר
                                                  ישראל</add> which I merely published to put<lb/>
                                        them to the trial, who came forward to uphold me and say let
                                        it published? it certainly<lb/> was not <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >Dedicated</hi> to some <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >one</hi>—but made all my brethren poor &amp; rich
                                                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>; 1000<lb/> are spent
                                        to get <hi rend="underline">honors</hi> &amp; <hi
                                                  rend="underline">titles</hi>. I have sent you my
                                        Dr. Sir a small sermon<lb/> through the hand of
                                                  <persName>Mr. Hart</persName> which no doubt you
                                        have received. I have<lb/> had no answer still from the said
                                        gentlemen on my second letter to him <date>19th<lb/>
                                                  Adar</date> a reply to his remarks my conclusion
                                        to him was as follows "I addressed<lb/> myself to you
                                        candidly as a person of high station and reputation, and
                                        also<lb/> as a friend of <persName>Revd. Mr.
                                                  Leeser</persName> of whom I have formed a very
                                        high opinion<lb/> and for whom I entertain great respect,
                                        admiring his talents, and<lb/> conceiving him to be a man
                                        worthy of honor and a <add>על כל פשעים תכסה אהבה</add>
                                        &amp;c and with<lb/> your own words "that He has done more
                                        for the Jews in <placeName>America</placeName> than any<lb/>
                                        other Hazan." and who after 20 years in office, and now
                                        should<lb/> be <hi rend="underline">out</hi> of <hi
                                                  rend="underline">office</hi>, I cannot but regard
                                        not only with regret—but as a<lb/> calamity." and I
                                        continued that even some little you might<lb/> have been in
                                        the fault for <hi rend="underline">publishing</hi>—I fully
                                        trusted &amp; looked <hi rend="underline">from
                                        him</hi>,<lb/> and he might make use of my name to the whole
                                        of the congregation<lb/> regarding you <hi rend="underline"
                                                  ><add>נצטדק מה נאמר מה נדבר מה</add></hi> the love
                                        they <hi rend="underline">should</hi> cherish &amp; entertain<lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">for a great man like yourself and who
                                                  for 20 years instructed them the</hi><lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">word of God</hi>. I hope some of the
                                        words may have an effect. I solemnly<lb/> declare to you
                                        that I never felt for any one or God per your treatment.<lb/>
                                        <add>תעורר את ליבם לב האבן</add>—I would at once make
                                        friends with <persName>Mr. H.</persName> for really he<lb/>
                                        <add>למען תגבר עליהם ויהיה שלום בחילך שלוה בארמונותיך</add>
                                        appears to have been <hi rend="underline">your friend</hi>.
                                        I shall copy you his language<lb/> in his letter <date>25th
                                                  Shebat</date>. "When at the time he wrote the
                                        article he was aware</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>that <hi rend="underline">two</hi> of the three meetings were for
                                        special purposes &amp; at which the<lb/> members refused to
                                        allow any thing to be offered. (except for the purpose<lb/>
                                        called) but has also spoken of me in a manner unbecoming a
                                                  <hi rend="underline">friend</hi>,<lb/> let alone a
                                        friend of upwards of Twenty years standing, you will<lb/>
                                        therefore perceive that I cannot, as you say I may "freely
                                        communicate<lb/> with <persName>Mr. Leeser</persName> on the
                                        subject of your letter altho he has as you
                                        <del>say</del><lb/> remark cognizance of your intention to
                                        write me." you must excuse<lb/> my long letters and in the
                                        manner they are wrote I am awaiting your<lb/> immediate
                                        answer to this and let me know precisely <hi
                                                  rend="underline">how affairs stand</hi>.<lb/> no
                                        doubt all the candidates are on the <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >look</hi> out. In prayer to God may<lb/> He be
                                                  <add>אוהבך אשר בנפשך דורש ודובר</add> of all your
                                        opponents <add>שלום לך ולכולנו ותמך ה' בידך יצלח</add> that
                                        you<lb/> have been reelected in the sincere <add>הצעיר דוד
                                                  בכמוהר"ר רפאל מילדולה</add> wish of <add>ושלום לך
                                                  שנית</add><lb/>
                                        <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>
                                        <add>Hebrew</add> As n<add>?</add><lb/>
                                        <add>?</add> honor is such that I should not conceal
                                                  <add>?</add><lb/>
                                        <add>?</add> thing from you, I deem it proper to send you a
                                        correct copy of <add>?</add><lb/>
                                        <add>?</add> in <persName>Mr. H</persName> letter to me, at
                                        the same time I must repeat any<lb/> part depending on your
                                        honor you will make use of them to save you only<lb/> but
                                        that my name be not mingled or to be made <add>?</add>—I
                                        trust to<lb/> you on this! "<hi rend="underline">I now
                                                  desire</hi> to state for your information that the
                                        late<lb/> misunderstanding between <persName>Mr
                                                  Leeser</persName> and this congregation tis
                                        between<lb/> the <add>?</add>pass of a nut shell, and
                                                  <persName>Mr. Leeser</persName> can only blame
                                        himself<lb/> (not his friend or the congregation) if he now
                                        finds that he has placed<lb/> himself by his own obstinacy
                                        in so unenviable a position for a man<lb/> of his high
                                        talents and learning" I expect your reply<lb/> as soon as
                                        possible that some good has been effected by your <hi
                                                  rend="underline">party</hi><lb/>
                                        <add>Hebrew</add></p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">America</hi>
                                        </placeName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
